Just a helpful tip. When asking "your name?" in urdu, there a few ways to do each same in meaning but varying in formality and respect similar to how Japanese use "san" or "sama" in varying situations. "Tera naam" is much too relaxed. It's not wrong but "tumhara naam?" is better and "ap ka naam?" is very formal.
Again, this isn't criticism, just helpful a tip for anyone interested.
